<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFF9FFC6FF71FDB9FE46FD5F" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFF9FFC6FF71FDB9FE33FD2B" blockId="17.[151,1437,582,753]" box="[151,462,619,645]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFF9FFC6FF79FDB9FF05FD2B" box="[159,248,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="63.[151,250,1933,1957]" captionTargetBox="[202,1388,194,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-19@63.[190,1397,181,1909]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURE 10. Eudocima salaminia and Eudocima discrepans group adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605520" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605520/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs 10</figureCitation>
: E–F, 19: H, 31: F)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFF9FFC6FF71FD5DFE46FD5F" blockId="17.[151,1437,582,753]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
This species is separated from similar 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF9FFC6FDB6FD5DFD22FD07" box="[592,735,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salaminia">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF9FFC6FDB6FD5DFD22FD07" box="[592,735,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">E. salaminia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as described above. It is endemic to New 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFF9FFC6FB2CFD5DFAE6FD07" box="[1226,1307,655,681]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Guinea</collectingCountry>
where it is found in the Central Highlands. In New 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFF9FFC6FDB5FD61FD59FD63" box="[595,676,691,717]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Guinea</collectingCountry>
it is sympatric with 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF9FFC6FC65FD61FBF2FD63" box="[899,1039,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salaminia">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF9FFC6FC65FD61FBF2FD63" box="[899,1039,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">E. salaminia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which is less common there (Papua Insects Foundation 2020).
</paragraph>
